  "body": "- [ ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nWhile writing a contract, if I write a test using `token.someMethod(arg1, arg2)`, it will execute. \r\n\r\nHowever, if I write a test with `token.someMethod.call(arg1, arg2)` it will _not execute_. \r\n\r\nIs this explicitly documented anywhere? its incredibly important.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nCreate an ERC20 token, use an implementation (I used OpenZeppelin), and fire up the following\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\ntruffle(development)> let thing = await ERC20Token.deploy();\r\n truffle(development)> thing.approve(accounts[1], 20);\r\n// truncated trasnaction output\r\n truffle(development)> thing.allowance(accounts[0], accounts[1]);\r\nBN { negative: 0, words: [ 20, <1 empty item> ], length: 1, red: null }\r\n truffle(development)> thing.allowance.call(accounts[0], accounts[1]);\r\nBN { negative: 0, words: [ 20, <1 empty item> ], length: 1, red: null }\r\n truffle(development)> thing.approve.call(accounts[1], 15);\r\ntrue\r\n truffle(development)> thing.allowance.call(accounts[0], accounts[1]);  // THIS IS INCORRECT\r\nBN { negative: 0, words: [ 20, <1 empty item> ], length: 1, red: null }\r\n truffle(development)> thing.approve.call(accounts[1], 15);\r\ntrue\r\n truffle(development)> thing.allowance.call(accounts[0], accounts[1]);\r\nBN { negative: 0, words: [ 20, <1 empty item> ], length: 1, red: null }\r\n truffle(development)> thing.approve(accounts[1], 15);\r\n// truncated transaction output\r\n truffle(development)> thing.allowance(accounts[0], accounts[1]);\r\nBN { negative: 0, words: [ 15, <1 empty item> ], length: 1, red: null }\r\n truffle(development)> .exit\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nI expected `.someMethod.call(args)` and `.someMethod(args)` to execute the same way.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nBoth functions did not execute the same way -- one didn't execute at all\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Ubuntu 20.04.2 LTS x86_64\r\n* Ethereum client: Not sure? Solc is 0.8.0\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): Truffle v5.3.7 (core: 5.3.7)\r\n* node version (`node --version`):  v15.14.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`):  7.7.6\r\n",
