    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Yes, exactly.  The `.call` method is for performing a call rather than a transaction.  More specifically:\r\n\r\n* `method.sendTransaction()` will always perform a transaction (and get the transaction's receipt, among other things)\r\n* `method.call`() will always perform a call (as in, do not perform a transaction, but do get the method's return value)\r\n* `method()` will perform a call for methods that are `view` or `pure`, and a transaction otherwise.\r\n\r\nThis actually is documented [here](https://www.trufflesuite.com/docs/truffle/getting-started/interacting-with-your-contracts#special-methods-on-truffle-contract-objects), and in a few other places, although I'll admit it's probably not findable enough, and we should probably improve that.\r\n\r\nHope that's helpful!",
